<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF108-755-534  </DOCNO><DOCID>08 755 534.andM;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Newsbytes  May 29 1990* Full Text COPYRIGHT Newsbytes Inc. 1990.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>IBM Japan creates object-oriented programming language. (C withOBjects)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Takahashi, Ken.andM;</AUTHOR><DESCRIPT>Company:   IBM Japan Ltd. (product development).andO;Topic:     EnhancementsProduct DevelopmentC Programming LanguageObject-Oriented Languages.andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>IBM JAPAN CREATES OBJECT-ORIENTED PROGRAMMING LANGUAGE TOKYO, JAPAN, 1990 MAY18 (NB) -- IBM Japan, the Japanese arm of U.S.- based computer giant IBM, hascreated a new C programming language with which computer software can bewritten.andM;Named COB or C with OBjects, the new language is a C language incorporatingseveral &quot;object-oriented&quot; features.andP;  Object-oriented programming allows aprogrammer to write a program by composing objects, each of which represent acombination of data processing features.andM;The COB is designed to make the writing of programs easier.andM;C++ created by ATandamp;T is a major object-oriented language based on the Clanguage, but IBM Japan claims that its COB is superior in that it hasenhanced features to find and erase errors or bugs.andP;  Also, IBM Japan says itslanguage enables a program to be created in one-tenth the time that the Clanguage requires.andM;(Ken Takahashi/19900524)</TEXT></DOC>